因为营销号说花岗岩能治新冠，日本墓碑断货了。
Because marketing numbers say granite cures the crown, Japan's tombstone is out of stock.
地球人研究报告。
Earthman Study Report.
趣闻。
Interesting news.
养生和伪科学在哪里都是营销号喜欢的土壤。
Healthcare and pseudoscience are where marketing numbers like the soil.
。
.
国际疫情扩散的档口上，继韩国囤辣酱，意大利人囤意大利面后，最先开始囤卫生纸的日本又有了新动作。
Japan, which has been hoarding toilet paper for the first time since the arrival of hot sauce in the country and pasta in Italy, is the first country where the disease has spread, according to the source.
。
.
有消息称，日本方面已经开始囤墓碑了。
Sources say the Japanese have begun hoarding tombstones.
。
.
囤墓碑这样的说法乍一听似乎有夸张之嫌，但这个信息来源出于朝日新闻的消息，显然不会是无中生有。
At first glance, the claim that the gravestone is a tombstone may sound exaggerated, but the source, which comes from Asahi News, is clearly not fake.
能让墓碑行业陷入困境的原因只有一种，就是作为原材料的花岗岩石料供应不足。
The only reason the tombstone industry is in trouble is the lack of supplies of granite as raw materials.
巧的是，就是因为一些阴差阳错的事故，让日本的花岗岩石料几乎一夜之间陷入了内外交困的局面。
Coincidentally, just because of some misguided accident, Japan's granite stone almost overnight into a situation of internal and diplomatic distress.
。
.
一切的缘起，都要从一则营销号的文章说起。
The origin of all, from a marketing number of the article began.
。
.
“花岗岩可以治疗新冠肺炎”。
"Granite can treat new crown pneumonia."
趁着时下的“热点”，为了贩卖自家含有花岗石成分的产品，日本一家三流营销号不嫌事大地放出消息称：花岗岩可以治疗新冠肺炎。
In an effort to sell its granite-containing products in the hot spot, a third-rate Japanese marketing firm has announced that granite can cure pneumonia.
。
.
他们这里的说辞是——。
What they say here is -.
绳文时代，有一股文明专门用花岗岩为老百姓治病，为花岗岩的神秘性打下基础；再到几十年前，某某某科学家意外地发现了花岗岩的奇效；最后结合实事，用一堆看不懂的科学名词告诉你花岗岩石如何消灭新冠病毒的。
In the age of rope, there was a civilization dedicated to treating the common people with granite, laying the foundation for granite mystique; and a few decades ago, scientists of So-and-so stumbled upon the wonders of granite; and finally, in a pile of unintelligible scientific terms, they told you how granite could destroy the new crown virus.
。
.
——瞧瞧这个带节奏的套路，国内观众早就再熟悉不过了，鉴于这篇文章实在太长，就翻译第一句话吧：。
Look at the rhythm of this routine, the domestic audience has long been familiar with it, given that this article is too long to translate the first sentence.
“作为新冠病毒的治疗对策，我推荐花岗岩。
"As a therapeutic response to the new crown virus, I recommend granite.
”。
"
其中提到的治疗原理，简言之就是：。
Healing principles mentioned therein, in short:
花岗岩可以释放出一种，特殊的紫外线，可以精准杀死新冠病毒的同时，还不会对人体产生任何损害。
Granite can release a special type of ultraviolet light that can kill the new canopy virus without causing any damage to the human body.
。
.
“花岗岩杀病毒”正常人看来是天方夜谭，而被营销号荼毒多年的国内观众来说，这种哗众取宠的套路甚至早就没什么新意了。
"Granite virus" normal people seem to be a myth, and the marketing of the long-term domestic audience, this kind of grandstanding routines have long been nothing new.
但是在日本，这个营销号的半处女地，杀伤力依然强大。
But in Japan, this semi-virgin land of marketing numbers, the lethality is still strong.
。
.
就这么一个不留神，夹杂着对新冠病毒的恐慌情绪，日本老百姓之间突然爆发了一波抢墓碑原料“花岗岩”的风潮。
With such carelessness and fear of the new crown virus, a wave of gravestone gravestone granite erupted among ordinary Japanese.
一时间，许多电商平台的花岗岩石料瞬间售空：。
For a while, the granite stone of many electric commerce platform sells short instantaneously:.
富士电视台旗下的FNN一看势头不对，赶紧在3月3日以 ｢花岗岩高价售卖，网传‘对新冠病毒有奇效’——形成新型冠状骚动｣ 为标题对该事件进行了报导：。
Fuji TV's FNN, which appeared to be in the wrong mood, rushed to cover the incident on March 3 with a fake granite sale at a premium, featuring a new type of crowning disturbance hospital.
里面显示对对日本老百姓抢花岗岩的事态其进行了说明，比如援引了一些推特发言：。
It shows the story of plundering granite against ordinary Japanese, citing tweets, for example:
现在河边上都捡不到花岗岩了！！。
There's no granite left on the river!!
走啊，咱上多摩川捡花岗岩去啊。
Come on, let's go pick up granite in Domokawa.
。
.
还采访了普通民众对此事的看法：。
The views of the general public on the matter were also interviewed.
路人：“知道知道，我看Mercari上有卖的，还寻思啊咋还卖石头呢。
Passerby: "You know, I see Mercari has sold, also think ah how I still sell stones.
”。
"
记者：“然后你就买了点？”。
Interviewer: "And you bought some?"
路人：“哈哈没买，咱又不懂。
Passerby: I didn't buy it. I don't know.
”。
"
（注：Mercari，日本C2C二手交易平台，可以理解为国外的闲鱼）。
(Note: Mercari, Japanese C2C second-hand trading platform, can be understood as foreign fish).
最后报道中苦口婆心地告诉观众：这玩意初中课本上就说了，什么效果都没有；甚至还搬出了各种科研机构的研究报告，对花岗石消灭新冠病毒可行性进行了全面否定。
In the final report, the audience was told bitterly that nothing had happened in the textbook of junior high school, and even studies by various scientific institutions had been cited to deny that granite was viable for the eradication of the new crown virus.
。
.
紧随其后的，雅虎等新闻网站也对“花岗岩疗法”进行了辟谣，大意是“谨防谣言，无科学根据”。
Yahoo and other news sites followed suit, denying rumors of granite therapy, to the effect that "there is no scientific basis for rumors."
。
.
但理性辟谣的新闻，跟跌宕起伏的营销号故事想比，效果杯水车薪。
But the rational refutation news, with the ups and downs of the marketing number story to compare, the effect is small.
。
.
先看日本最主流的搜索引擎吧，雅虎搜索的联想里，花岗岩有关的词条已经全数沦陷：。
Look at the most mainstream search engine in Japan, Yahoo search Lenovo, granite-related terms have all fallen:
再看电商平台。
Look at the TV commercial platform.
日本的Mercari上，大大小小的花岗岩商品还是出于几乎全面售罄的状况。
On Mercari in Japan, granite commodities, large and small, are almost completely sold out.
。
.
到这个时候，一份河边上就能捡到的花岗岩石头，最贵的已经被炒到了12000日元，折合人民币约800元。
By this time, the most expensive granite stone that can be found on the river has been fired at 12,000 yen, equivalent to about 800 yuan.
。
.
另一边，推特上，身为抢花岗岩的民众的同胞日本网友们也气乐了，他们一边大呼荒唐， 一边……不忘了传统艺能“玩梗”。
On the other hand, Twitter, the Japanese netizens, fellow granite plunderers, are also amused by the absurdity of yelling... not forgetting that traditional art can be "tricky."
。
.
一家眼镜店老板“執事眼鏡ツネタ社長”趁机让自家产品搭便车：。
An eyeglass shop owner "executive eyeglasses turn out to be a martyr" takes the opportunity to hitch his product.
我们这款花岗石太阳镜，不仅能防止眼部飞沫传染，目光所及之处还能直接杀死新冠病毒（误）。
Our granite sunglasses not only prevent eye froth, but also directly kill the new crown virus wherever you look.
。
.
而家里曾经保有花岗石相关产品的网友，此时翻出那些老掉牙的古董时更是如获至宝，一个个跑出来炫耀：。
And the family once held granite-related products netizens, at this time turned out those old antique is like a treasure, one by one run out to show off:
听说花岗岩对新冠病毒有奇效，我预感到我的FM77AV40SX要涨价了。
I heard that granite has worked wonders for the new crown virus, and I had a hunch that my FM 77AV40SX was going up.
↓。
Dell Computers
（注：FM77AV40SX这款富士通的电脑因采用灰黑配色，被圈内人戏称为“墓碑PC”）。
(Note: FM 77AV40SX This Fujitsu computer has been dubbed Tombstone PC by insiders because of its gray-and-black color.
“虽然没有花岗岩，但我感觉自家的紫晶石还能勉强对付一下——SweetchesP@twi”。
"There's no granite, but I feel my own purple crystal can barely cope with it - Sweetches P @ twi."
“跟花岗岩有关的东西，家里只剩下这个了——akimogumogu@twi”。
"This is all that's left of granite - akimogumogu @ twi."
而且即便是家里实在翻不出花岗岩，老百姓们还能找到办法诉诸于虚拟世界，想方设法捣腾出花岗岩来自救。
And even if the family really can not turn over granite, people can still find a way to resort to virtual world, find ways to tamper with granite from the rescue.
。
.
这其中，盛产“花岗岩”的《我的世界》就是一个很好的“挖矿”途径。
Among them, the "granite-rich" "My World" is a good way to "mine."
物资抢手到这种程度，商业头脑过人的一些玩家，甚至已经抢先一步在二手网站把自己多余的花岗岩材料上架了：。
To such a degree, some business-savvy players have even pre-empted their superfluous granite materials on second-hand sites:
“成色：有轻微擦痕”。
"Success: There are slight scratches."
卖不卖得出去另说，至少能秀了一波自己的“资产实力”。
Can not sell out to say otherwise, at least a wave of their own "asset strength."
。
.
雪上加霜的日本墓碑行业。
Add to that Japan's tombstone industry.
在日本，人死后有立花岗岩墓碑的习俗。
In Japan, it is customary to erect granite tombstones after death.
。
.
因为这次的抢花岗岩风暴的爆发，让一些人自然而然地想到了最丰富的花岗岩聚集地——墓地。
As a result of the granite storm, some people naturally think of the most abundant granite gathering place - the cemetery.
本来，他们也就是想借此对“抢花岗岩”的迷惑行为做一下吐槽：。
Originally, they also want to use this to "rob granite" bewildering behavior to do a groove:.
这么想要花岗岩的话，死了之后就能过着被花岗岩环绕的生活了（指墓碑）。
If you want granite so much, you can live a life surrounded by granite when you die.
但，也许这位小姐姐不知道的是，照他们同胞对花岗岩的这个抢法，今后这个智商可能也就用不到墓碑了。
What the little sister did not know, however, was that, in the light of the granite robbery of their countrymen, the IQ might no longer be used as a tombstone.
。
.
就像另个一位朋友担忧的那样：。
As another friend worries:
我看FNN新闻上都报高价贩卖花岗岩的事了，这玩意要是引发盗墓者的横行可咋整啊。
I think the FNN news reports high-priced granite sales, which can be quite shocking if it triggers grave robbers.
。
.
“墓碑流”的盗墓，光是听听就觉得魔幻。
"Tombstone flow" tomb theft, just listen to feel magic.
还真让他们说着了，因为花岗岩的“被抢”，最直接受到冲击的，就是日本的墓碑行业。
Let them really say, because the granite "robbed", the most direct impact of the Japanese tombstone industry.
。
.
开头提到的“囤墓碑”传闻的来源出自朝日新闻2月28日的报导。
The source of the headstone rumor, according to the Asahi Shimbun, Feb. 28, 2007.
因墓碑供应不足问题接受采访的是武蔵石材店。
Hidden stone shops were interviewed about the shortage of tombstones.
。
.
这是一家服务于东京都内的大型墓碑店，现任社长是创始人的孙子——用他们官网上的说法，就是“三代目”井冈进。
This is a large tombstone shop in Tokyo, and its current president is the founder's grandson, who, in the words of their official website, is "Three Generations" Igawa.
武蔵石材店的网站宣传页面上，自己墓碑生意一直不错的三代目笑得还挺灿烂的：。
Hidden stone shop advertising page on the website, his tombstone business has been good three generations of eye-catching smile quite bright:.
平时的墓碑·三代目。
The Tombstone: Three Generations.
但现在，面对朝日新闻记者，采访中的三代目面露难色，语调中还带着哭腔：。
But now, the face of the Asahi News reporter, the interview of the three generations of the face, tone of voice with crying:
现在的状况就是石头完全进不来了。
As it stands now, the stone won't get in at all.
。
.
疫情下的墓碑·三代目。
Tombstone under the Epidemic: Three Generations.
三代目指的“进不来”，是指日本所用的花岗岩石材，70-80%都是源于中国进口。
Three generations of granite stones used in Japan, 70 to 80 percent of which are imported from China.
因为疫情原因，中国方面的原料输送几乎停滞了。
The flow of raw materials from China has almost ground to a halt because of the outbreak.
。
.
当然，“70-80%”这个数据的另一方面，也意味着至少还有两成多的花岗岩产能，是可以靠日本国内自己消化的。
The other side of the 70-80% figure, of course, also means that at least 20% more granite production capacity can be absorbed by Japan itself.
。
.
这为数不多的自主花岗岩产能，对墓碑行业来说总算是不幸中的万幸了。
This few independent granite production capacity, for the tombstone industry is unfortunately fortunate.
。
.
但是！就是因为日本老百姓盲目地争抢花岗岩，这一下子把日本国内的石料路子也给断了。
But just because the Japanese people blindly scrambled for granite, this suddenly broke the stone path in Japan.
而且墓碑行业还不像电子产品、生活用品这种，要么供应商有一定的备货，要么老百姓忍一忍就过去了。
And the tombstone industry is not like electronic products, such as daily necessities, or suppliers have a certain amount of stock, or the common people endure the past.
。
.
但墓碑不行，来一个就是绝对的刚需。
But tombstones can't. One is absolutely just needed.
。
.
那么现在紧缺状态到了哪个阶段了呢？2月28日报道中显示，已经有5个客人正在等自己的墓碑到货：。
So where is the current shortage? Five guests are waiting for their tombstones to arrive, the Feb. 28 report said.
这也意味着之前的库存已经几乎消耗殆尽。
This also means that previous inventories have been almost depleted.
且只要疫情一天不结束，这个墓碑的缺口就会越拉越大。
And as long as the epidemic does not end, the gap in the tombstone will widen.
。
.
但事情发展到这个时候， 墓碑店老板们已经有劲也使不出了。
But by the time things got to this point, Tombstone's owners were struggling too.
。
.
